<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,151,580]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,227,252]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Identification.</emphasis>
Test moderate to large, aborally raised, and slightly elongated. Apical disc anteriorly positioned, monobasal, with four gonopores. Peristome wider than long, sub-centrally positioned; bourrelets and phyllodes distinct; five well-developed petals, extending to edge, distally opened; anterior-lateral petals being the shortest, sub-equal. Posterior interambulacrum sometimes having a naked space, not raised towards peristome, tuberculation and spines dense, uniform, and becoming sparse towards peristomial area. Test and spine both brown.
</paragraph>
